T1  - Relationship of plasma protein Z with age, body mass index and fibrinogen in young patients with stroke of unknown origin
A1  - Wang T.-Y.
A1  - Tian G.-L.
A1  - Jiang S.
A1  - Wang J.-H.
Y1  - 2004//
N2  - Aim: To investigate the relation of plasma protein Z(PZ) with age, body mass index(BMI) and fibrinogen in the youth with cerebral infarction and cerebral hemorrhage of unknown origin for seeking the common risk factor of young stroke patients. Method(s): It was a case-control trial. Totally 33 young patients with cerebral infarction and 39 with cerebral hemorrhage whose etiological factors are unknown were selected from the Department of Neurology, Bohai Oil Hospital of Tianjin. And 78 subjects for health examination were enrolled as controls. Venous blood was extracted as blood sample. Level of PZ was measured with enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay. Result(s): PZ level was(2.85 +/- 0.69) mg /L in the cerebral infarction group, significantly higher than the control group[(2.07 +/- 0.80) mg/L], and there was a significant difference between the two groups(q = 6.197 7, P < 0.01). However, the level of PZ in the cerebral hemorrhage group was (1.22 +/- 0.53) mg/L, significantly lower than that in the control group(q = 4.644 8, P < 0.01). In the cerebral infarction group, the level of PZ had a positive relation with age, BMI, fibrinogen level(r = 0.505, 0.436, 0.620, P < 0.05). Conclusion(s): The increase of decrease of PZ level may relate to the stroke of unknown origin in the young, but it need further study.
