AN  - 39029728
T1  - Effect of genetic factor on cerebral infarction in young persons
A1  - Li F.-L.
A1  - Liu Q.-R.
A1  - Liu P.
Y1  - 2004//
N2  - Aim: To explore the role of genetic factor in the occurrence of cerebral infarction(CI) in the young patients. Method(s): A questionnaire was performed in 216 CI patients and 300 healthy young persons to collect family history of cardiovascular and cerebrovascular disease, including hypertension, coronary heart disease and cerebrovascular disease, and the data of first-degree relatives with CI except their children. A case-control study was conducted to evaluate risk rate of the young persons with CI history quantitatively and calculate heritability of CI. Result(s): CI family history was found in 69.9% of the CI young patients, significantly higher than that of the normal persons 18.67% (chi2 = 137.25, P < 0.001). The exposure rate to cardiovascular and cerebrovascular diseases was higher in the male or female cases than the healthy subjects(P < 0.01). The incidence of cardiovascular and cerebrovascular diseases was 51.85% in the mothers of CI patients, significantly higher than in the fathers of CI patients 18.06% (chi2 = 71.18, P < 0.001), and the CI heritability was (72 +/- 5)%. Family history of hypertension was found in 55.56% of the CI patients and 11.33% of the healthy subjects, and there was a significant difference between the two groups(chi 2 = 117.29, P < 0.001). Conclusion(s): Family history of cardiovascular and cerebrovascular diseases is a risk factor for CI in the young persons, and genetic factor plays an important role in the occurrence of CI.
